AI Assistant Project Roadmap
Current Version — Local AI Assistant with Memory ✅
The foundation of the project is a locally hosted AI assistant powered by an LLM running through Ollama.
Current capabilities:

Flask web application backend
Local LLM integration using Ollama
SQLite database for persistent conversation storage
Conversation history retrieval
Context formatting for AI conversations
Basic system prompting
Modular project structure:

app.py — application routes and request handling
database.py — database operations
ai.py — AI message preparation

Future Development Plans
Phase 1 — Improve Memory System ✅✅
Move from simple chat history storage to a proper memory system.
      Separate conversation history from long-term memories
      Create a dedicated memory database table
      Store important user facts separately from messages
      Add timestamps and memory categories
      Allow the assistant to retrieve relevant memories instead of sending the entire chat history

Phase 2 — Document Assistant Features ✅✅
Transform the project into a true AI document assistant.
      Upload documents (PDF, TXT, DOCX)
      Extract and process text
      Search documents using AI
      Ask questions about uploaded files
      Provide answers with relevant document context

Phase 3 — Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) 
Improve AI accuracy by retrieving relevant information before generating responses.
      Text chunking ✅
      Embeddings
      Vector database integration
      Semantic search
      Relevant context retrieval

Phase 4 — User Experience Improvements 
      Chat interface improvements
      Conversation history sidebar
      Multiple conversations
      User accounts
      File management
      Settings page  
      Model selection

Phase 5 — Production Improvements ⚙️
      Environment variables
      Better error handling
      Logging
      Database migrations
      Automated testing
      Deployment
      Security improvements

Long-Term Vision
A personal AI assistant that can remember useful information, understand uploaded documents, retrieve knowledge when needed, run locally for privacy, and provide a personalised assistant experience.
